Installation
MiPlatform has attracted much attention domestically for its RIA development platform based on X-internet. Anyframe provides MiPQueryService and MiPController to process MiPlatform-specific data type when developing application based on MiPlatform. MiPlatfor Plugin consists of sample code that provide basic guidelines on how to use MiPQueryService and MiPController that are MiPlatform connection modules provided by Anyframe, and reference libraries necessary for this.
&miplatform_installation;

Miplatform Integration



		Anyframe provides MiPQueryService and AnyframeMiPController to easily and conveniently connect with MiPlatform 
		that is a RIA development platform.


&miplatform_integration_mipcontroller;
&miplatform_integration_mipquery;

Miplatform Simplification
Miplatform uses a data type that is MiPlatform-specific to transfer data. The commonly used type is Dataset object. Dataset is only for MiPlatform, so for simple CRUD functions, server logic such as Java Generics can be used through common handling. Therefore, when application is developed based on MiPlatform, developer will be provided with a common server module so that Service or DAO does not have to be developed for implementing CRUD function that has no complex or special work logic.
&miplatform_simplification_mipservice;
